body_html:
What is the content of your APK?

We don't use Android/application.mk to build TF, so I would not suggest going down this path.

What OS are you developing on? You should be placing the libs in the "libs/" folders.

Also what version of TF are you using? There are currently no native methods in TensorFlowImageClassifier, so I don't see how this could be native libraries related with any recent release. And if you're changing package names you're really outside the scope of TF support.

body:
What is the content of your APK?

We don't use Android/application.mk to build TF, so I would not suggest going down this path.

What OS are you developing on? You should be placing the libs in the "libs/<target>" folders.

Also what version of TF are you using? There are currently no native methods in TensorFlowImageClassifier, so I don't see how this could be native libraries related with any recent release. And if you're changing package names you're really outside the scope of TF support.
